WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
This is an example of a subtitle track in VTT format.

00:02.000 --> 00:04.000
Subtitles can be used to translate the audio of a video into another language.

00:04.000 --> 00:06.000
They can also be used to provide additional information about the content of the video, such as identifying the characters who are speaking.

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
Subtitles are an important tool for making videos more accessible to people with hearing impairments or who do not understand the language of the audio.
